{"title":"Hooks on a server","tags":["open"],"date":"2009-11-23T22:17:18Z","author":"Simon Chiang <simon.chiang@pinnacol.com>","type":"issue","content":"Central servers could benefit from a post-commit hook that resets the repo.  This could be done in the form of a post-to-self:\r\n\r\n  /repo/update?reset=true\r\n\r\nThat will prevent the situation where the working tree shows removes... in fact this or something like it is necessary because otherwise the next commit will try to remove the missing items from the tree!","at":"bffe95f877288394457678942c7a5c2e166333b4","state":"open"}